article.headline: UC Riverside 94, UC Davis 87
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Larry Cunningham had a career-high 33 points and Steve Williams had career bests of 30 points and 15 rebounds as UC Riverside beat UC Davis 94-87 in overtime Saturday. Williams, a senior playing in his final home game, was 5-of-5 from behind the 3-point line as the Highlanders (5-22) rallied from 14 points down to force overtime. UC Riverside's Ricky Porter tied the game on a driving lay-up with 18 seconds left. Porter, who scored 19 points, made back-to-back 3-pointers with just over a minute left to bring the Highlanders within two points. In overtime, UC Davis (8-20) took a two-point lead 84-82 on a dunk by Michael Boone, but Cunningham scored seven points in the extra period and Williams made three free throws in the final 40 seconds to seal the win. Kyle Brucculeri led the Aggies with 26 points, Rommel Martinez scored 17 and David Carter had 16. The Aggies biggest lead was 59-45 with 13:16 to play. They still led by 10 with 3:22 remaining, but were outscored 12-2 the rest of the game. The Highlanders are the No. 8 seed in the Big West Conference tournament that begins Wednesday. They will play No. 5 seed UC Santa Barbara in the opening round.
